I"à<p>Proudly Serving is a work in progress and always gets better, especially with feedback from you.</p>

<h2 id="code-of-conduct">Code of conduct</h2>

<p>Please <a href="/conduct/">review the Proudly Serving code of conduct</a> before providing feedback.</p>

<h2 id="how-it-works">How it works</h2>

<ul>
  <li>Each chapter draft starts as a separate Google Doc.</li>
  <li>We issue an open call for feedback when the chapter draft is ready for public review.</li>
  <li>Anyone can add comments to the chapter draft.</li>
  <li>Once we finalize the chapter, we fold it into the main <a href="/manuscript/">manuscript</a>.</li>
  <li>Anyone can add comments to the main <a href="/manuscript/">manuscript</a> doc at anytime.</li>
</ul>
